<br>
She often did, 'those sort of jobs', for others, tasks that would normally not be undertaken, but that many were willing to pay quite handsomely for.<br>
<br>
She was an enchanter, and found Neriak a damp and dank place, full of stuffy conceited figure heads that didn't seem to care about anything other than their own position amongst themselves.<br>
<br>
Most cities seemed to be this way.<br>
<br>
Iteria, would seek out this new job, this Aedare person. Something about a cataloguing position, and reporting back to for acknowledgement.<br>
<br>
She had traversed through the commons, and used her magics to find a tracker, to locate Aedare.<br>
<br>
When she had reached within radius of the target, she had paid the tracker for his services with a knife in the neck. Iteria liked clean jobs. No sense, in anyone else knowing about her business. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uaedare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aedare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/10/01 3:26:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://dntsvara.tripod.com/aedarepic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aedare's Departure...</span><hr size=1> Passing through the Commonlands, I stopped at the Plague Village near the borders of Neriak.  It was a familiar place to me, as since our rejection by the Spires, Vanlaan and I had utilized it as a base of operations - a home, in far too many cases.<br>
<br>
I had arranged for a messenger, well in advance.  The question stood whether or not the messenger was trustworthy.<br>
<br>
When the robed dark elf slipped out from the shadows before me, I knew that he had been.<br>
<br>
&quot;You are?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Iteria.&quot;<br>
<br>
No fawning respect, nothing but a professional attitude.  Not appropriate for a true follower of the Father, which meant she was exactly what I wanted.<br>
<br>
&quot;And you are an enchantress?&quot;<br>
<br>
She simply nodded.  Her being of the Spurned made her suit my cause.  But what had she turned away from?  Our people?  Or Our Father?  Little enough matter; if my plans went well, I would find out easily enough.<br>
<br>
&quot;You may care little for this, but listen anyway.  I represent the Church of the Firstborn.  As you probably know, the Firstborn and the Spires have become divided over how Neriak society should be run.  We should all be one people, following our Father's call.  Instead, we are a race of self-serving creatures who give no thought to His Glory when it does not serve us.<br>
<br>
&quot;Do I wish this to change?  Yes.  Is this why I have called you?  No.  The Spires has named one Spurned who does not deserve it.  I can be Spurned, for I was born human...&quot;<br>
<br>
She tried to hide her shock and disgust.  She failed.  Again, of little consequence.<br>
<br>
&quot;As I was saying, I can be Spurned, but Vanlaan cannot.  He is a true follower of the Will and the Way, and is too fragile to not feel that he is firmly connected to his home.  I seek to have the Spires renounce their statements about him.  To do so, I need to impress them, and my fellow dark elves, into ignoring the shouts of one of their members.<br>
<br>
&quot;That's where you come in.  I need to become... bigger than I am.  I need to become something of a legend, someone that the Dark Elves see as being the direct avatar of Innoruuk.&quot;  She laughed at that, and I shrugged.  &quot;Blasphemy, perhaps.  But if you can write in the style of the Old Books, perhaps we can pull this off.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;And the payment?&quot;<br>
<br>
I reached under a loose board and brought out a shimmering wooden staff.  In the torchlight outside the house, runes glittered.  &quot;This... is a runed totem staff, an old weapon of Vanlaan's.  He was keeping it in case we needed a bargaining posture at some point.  It is yours, as is a full share of the treasure we may find on our explorations of Norrath.  After all, for someone who turned from Neriak's ways to learn, there must be little that is more valuable to you than a chance to increase your learning, yes?&quot;<br>
<br>
I could see the greed in her eyes, but I sat back to hear her response. <p>Innoruuk Guides My Path,
Aedare - "The Blade of L'vanon"
Spurned Shadow Knight of Innoruuk
(Ayonae Ro Server)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uiteria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Iteria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New to the block</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/12/01 4:13:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aedare's Departure...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> From the Chronicles of Aedare, as scribed by Iteria<br>
the Enchantress:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
And so it came to pass that Aedare Truedark, Champion of Innoruuk, did slay one of The Father's Hated Enemies near the gate of the Marr's City, within sight of one of the Marr's Children.<br>
<br>
And lo, having slain this most unworthy foe, Aedare removed his head from his body, and bore it from Freeport through the Commonlands, and into the Father's Beloved forest.  Her actions angered the souls of the Hated Others, and one of them rose from the dead to do battle with her.  But, upon seeing the Most Holy Hatred in her eyes, it bowed under her and offered its weapon for her use.  And Aedare nodded,<br>
for it was good in the Father's sight.<br>
<br>
With the head of the Hated One in one hand and the Fallen One's weapon in the Other, Aedare crossed into Neriak, and all eyes were upon her.  Many followed her past the Third Gate, and many watched as she stood proudly before the walls of the Spires.  And those within the Spires cowered in fear, for Innoruuk's Hand was upon her, and Innoruuk's Hatred burned in her eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Hear me, oh Faithful!&quot; Aedare cried, and those in the Spires could not help but listen.  &quot;I hold in my hand the head of Our Enemy's Faithful, which I give to you in honor.&quot;  <br>
<br>
But none stirred within the Spires. And thus did Aedare take up the spear from the Fallen One, and thrust it into the ground with all her might; and though the ground before the spires was made of purest marble, and though the blade of the spear was covered with rust, it pierced through the ground with such force that thirteen of the strongest men could not pull it out.  And upon that spear she placed the head of the Hated Paladin of Marr.  But still none stirred.<br>
<br>
&quot;Still you do not answer my plea,&quot; Aedare called out once more.  &quot;I hold in my hand that Hated One's Testimony of Truth, the sum of his faith.  In Innoruuk's Holy Fires, I destroy this testament to do honor to the Father.&quot;  But still none stirred.  And with the torches that stood before the Spires, Aedare set the Testimony aflame; and as it burned, those around could hear the sounds of screaming, as though the Marrs Themselves cried out in pain.<br>
<br>
&quot;Most honored lords,&quot; cried Most Holy Aedare, &quot;I have done battle with the enemy in Innoruuk's Name.  And to you I bring the trophies of this battle.  Does this action not deserve a moment of your time?&quot;<br>
<br>
But one who hid his visage from the Father with a mask did step on the battlements of the Spires, and speak thusly to Aedare. &quot;Thirteen enemies of the Father may you kill, and thirteen times thirteen, but the Spires will not listen.  For I have turned them from their True Path, and they shall not follow the Will and the Way.&quot;  <br>
<br>
And with laughter, that one turned away, but Aedare knew from his voice that this was Aravs, who had turned from the Father's Teachings and had been seen in the company of the Hated Others for many turns of the moon.  And Aedare fell to her knees, and wept that such a noble force should be turned away from the Father.<br>
<br>
But her Hatred was strong, and so was her resolve. &quot;If thirteen will not suffice, and thirteen times thirteen still not be enough, then shall I slay thirteen times those.  The trees of Norrath will feast on the blood of His Enemies, and the Father will rule those whom He allows me to leave alive.  Until the Spires hears my plea, and Hated Aravs be torn from those battlements, let none who dwell in the light rest easy, for Aedare, the blade of Most Holy L'vanon brings His Most Holy Hatred to them all!&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=12.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=12.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=12.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.threadControl?topicID=12.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=12.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=12.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><t